cs.NE, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.LG, cs.MA 

The paper deals with optimizing the performance of a UAV-assisted wireless network using a deep reinforcement learning algorithm. The problem involves optimizing the flight trajectory of the UAV and scheduling of status update packets to minimize the age-of-information (AoI) values of different processes at the UAV. This problem involves a combination of network optimization, control theory, and machine learning. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper are cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), cs.IT (Information Theory), cs.SY (Systems and Control), cs.LG (Machine Learning), and cs.MA (Multiagent Systems).
